    <div class="body">
      I'm really appalled that a person who was the leader of the CIA at one point would think it would even be ok to say such things in a public forum.  I am sure that all of us can agree that saying something in private, or even to oneself might contain something like this, or even trash talk on gaming channels, where the mentality is a bit lower than your average adult conversation.  But someone who has risen through the ranks and been entrusted with such a role should know where personal views should be left.  This gentleman should be publicly reprimanded and his viewpoint should be left to himself!  I do not know the legal ramifications, but some public watchdog group should be up in arms here.  Snowden, while no longer a US resident, cannot legally take this person to court over libel, since to do so would require him to file legal proceedings in the US, where he would immediately be taken into custody, but someone should take this guy to task!
      
